---

@fn new_table
@sig () -> SymbolTable
@source_file src/resolver/scope.aria
@source_line 109
@purpose Creates a new SymbolTable pre-populated with sentinel entries at index 0 for both scopes and symbols. The sentinel ensures index 0 is never a valid reference, simplifying "not found" checks.
@post scopes.len() == 1 and symbols.len() == 1 (both contain only sentinels).

---

@fn add_scope
@sig (table: SymbolTable, kind: ScopeKind, parent: i64, name: str) -> SymbolTable
@source_file src/resolver/scope.aria
@source_line 115
@purpose Appends a new scope to the table, automatically computing its depth from the parent scope's depth + 1. Returns a new SymbolTable (functional style).
@pre parent must be a valid scope ID (0 <= parent < table.scopes.len()), or 0 for top-level.
@post The new scope's ID is table.scopes.len() - 1 in the returned table.
@effects Allocates a new scopes array (append creates a copy).

---

@fn last_scope_id
@sig (table: SymbolTable) -> i64
@source_file src/resolver/scope.aria
@source_line 127
@purpose Returns the ID of the most recently added scope. Used immediately after add_scope to capture the new scope's ID for current_scope tracking.

