---

@fn lookup_local
@sig (table: SymbolTable, scope_id: i64, name: str) -> Symbol
@source_file src/resolver/scope.aria
@source_line 142
@purpose Searches for a symbol by name within a single specific scope only, without walking the parent chain. Returns the sentinel symbol (name="") if not found. Used for duplicate-declaration checking within the same scope.
@pre scope_id must be a valid scope ID.
@post Returns a Symbol with name="" if no match found; otherwise returns the first matching symbol.
@notes Linear scan over all symbols, skipping sentinel at index 0. Performance is O(n) in total symbol count. Adequate for compiler-sized programs but would need optimization for very large codebases.

---

@fn lookup
@sig (table: SymbolTable, scope_id: i64, name: str) -> Symbol
@source_file src/resolver/scope.aria
@source_line 157
@purpose Searches for a symbol by walking up the scope chain from scope_id through all ancestor scopes to the universe scope. This is the primary name resolution mechanism. Returns the sentinel symbol if the name is not found in any enclosing scope.
@pre scope_id must be a valid scope ID or 0.
@post Returns the first matching symbol found in the nearest enclosing scope, or sentinel if not found anywhere.
@notes Walks from the given scope to parent, grandparent, etc., calling lookup_local at each level. Stops when cur reaches 0 (sentinel scope, which has no symbols). Does NOT check scope 0 for symbols (the sentinel scope should never contain real symbols).

---

@fn resolve
@sig (tokens: [Token], index: DeclIndex, pool: NodePool, file: str) -> ResolveResult
@calls [new_table, add_scope, add_symbol, lookup, lookup_local]
@source_file src/resolver/resolver.aria
@source_line 2103
@purpose Main entry point for name resolution. Performs the complete two-pass resolution algorithm: creates the scope hierarchy (universe -> module), populates builtins (including assertEqual, assertOk, assertErr, assertNear, dbg), collects top-level declarations (Pass 1), then resolves all identifier references in function/entry/test/const/impl bodies (Pass 2).
@pre tokens must be a valid token stream from the lexer. index must be a valid DeclIndex from the parser. pool must be the NodePool from the parser. file must be the source file path.
@post Returns a ResolveResult containing the complete SymbolTable and any diagnostics. The symbol table contains all scopes and symbols for the entire file.
@effects Allocates the entire scope/symbol infrastructure. No I/O.
@workflow Called by the compilation pipeline after parsing. The returned SymbolTable is passed to the checker along with the AST. Diagnostics are merged with checker diagnostics for final reporting.
@errors E0701 "unresolved name" -- identifier not found in any enclosing scope (includes "did you mean?" suggestion via edit distance). E0702 "duplicate declaration" -- two declarations with the same name in the same scope. E0704 "symbol is private" -- accessing a non-pub symbol from a different file. W0004 "variable shadows previous declaration" -- a new binding shadows an existing non-builtin symbol in an enclosing scope.
@notes Pass 1 iterates the DeclIndex to register: use (as SkModule), fn (as SkFunction, including extern fn blocks), type/struct (as SkType, plus SkVariant for sum type variants), enum (as SkEnum), trait (as SkTrait), const (as SkConst). Entry, test, and impl blocks are skipped in Pass 1. Pass 2 iterates the DeclIndex again: fn/entry/test/const/impl declarations are resolved using either AST-based walking (if node_idx > 0) or legacy token-walking fallback. Type/enum/trait/use declarations are skipped in Pass 2 (no body resolution needed). The AST-based walker (_resolve_expr_node) handles all expression kinds including bindings (:=), closures, match patterns, for loops, with statements, catch blocks, select expressions, list comprehensions, and string interpolation. The legacy token-walking path remains for impl methods and extern/fixture declarations that lack AST nodes.
